{"id":898894956,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1Â month","timestamp":1676520456,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"3 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/898894956/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Two Sum IV - Input is a BST","memory":"42.7 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for a binary tree node.\n * public class TreeNode {\n *     int val;\n *     TreeNode left;\n *     TreeNode right;\n *     TreeNode() {}\n *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\n *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {\n *         this.val = val;\n *         this.left = left;\n *         this.right = right;\n *     }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n    \n    private Map<Integer,Boolean> map = new HashMap<>();\n    private int k;\n\n    public boolean findTarget(TreeNode root, int k) {\n        if(root == null) return false;        \n        this.k = k;\n        return traverse(root);\n    }\n\n    private boolean traverse(TreeNode root){\n        if(root == null) return false;\n\n        if(map.containsKey(k-root.val)) return true;\n\n        map.put(root.val,true);\n\n        return traverse(root.left) || traverse(root.right);\n    }\n\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"two-sum-iv-input-is-a-bst","has_notes":false}
